articles.headline: UCF: Shawn Clark in stable condition after medical emergency
articles.description: UCF offensive line coach Shawn Clark is hospitalized in stable condition after experiencing a medical emergency Tuesday night.

articles.headline: LSU's Brian Kelly: SEC coaches unified on new portal dates
articles.description: SEC coaches say they are in favor of the proposed move of college football's transfer portal window from December to January, arguing it's the best option even if it conflicts with the College Football Playoff schedule.

articles.headline: Finebaum: College football portal dates will affect everything
articles.description: Paul Finebaum joins "The Rich Eisen Show" to discuss the NCAA opening a college football transfer portal in January.

articles.headline: Who are the winningest college football coaches of all time?
articles.description: From Saban to Paterno, there are many legendary college football coaches. Who has the best career record? Check out who has the most wins now.

articles.headline: Sources: Missouri QB Sam Horn to miss season after leg surgery
articles.description: Missouri QB Sam Horn underwent surgery to repair a fractured tibia in his right leg and is expected to miss the rest of the season, sources told ESPN's Pete Thamel on Wednesday.

articles.headline: Alabama WR Ryan Williams on track to play vs. Wisconsin
articles.description: Alabama wide receiver Ryan Williams, who suffered a concussion in the season opener, should be available to play against Wisconsin, coach Kalen DeBoer said.

images.caption: DeBoer elaborates on the adjustments and improvement following the Week 1 loss and discusses the No. 19 Tide's injury list while looking ahead to Wisconsin.
